#### Important Equations

1. **Total Parameters in a Feed-Forward Network (FFN) Block**
   \[
   \text{Total parameters} = (d_{\text{model}} \times \text{hidden size} + \text{hidden size}) + (\text{hidden size} \times d_{\text{model}} + d_{\text{model}})
   \]
   Where \(d_{\text{model}}\) is the embedding dimension and \(\text{hidden size}\) is the size of the hidden layer.

2. **GPU Memory for Optimizer States**
   \[
   \text{GPU Memory (GB)} = \frac{\text{Total Parameters} \times 2 \times 4 \text{ bytes}}{10^9}
   \]
   This equation calculates the memory required for storing optimizer states, where each parameter has 2 floating-point values (for Adam optimizer) and each value is a 32-bit float (4 bytes).

3. **Vocabulary Size After BPE Merge**
   \[
   \text{New Vocabulary Size} = \text{Initial Vocabulary Size} + 1
   \]
   This equation represents the increase in vocabulary size after performing one merge operation in Byte Pair Encoding (BPE).

